    "body": "This is not a bug, but  a \"feature\" :sweat_smile: \r\n\r\nWe removed the back up of the private key on waku, so it's normal that you are not recognized as a control node.\r\n\r\nThe tokenized ownership is going to be done in 0.15.\r\n\r\nFor now, having the Owner token is just a way to make sure on chain that only owners and tokenMasters can deploy and mint community tokens.\r\n\r\nThe only way to become a control node again is to import the community's private key. If you didn't back it up before deleting the data folder, then that community is lost sadly.",
