    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> oh my , so even i have Owner token - it is still like that? what is the token for then :D @jrainville\r\n\r\nIt's an on-chain validation mechanism to make sure that only accounts that are Owner or TokenMaster can interact with community tokens.\r\n\r\nFor example, if there is the token called StatusCommunityToken that is for the Status Community, we not only do a check in our code to make sure that no one can mint that token except Owners and TokenMasters, but the OwnerToken And TokenMaster contract is also checked, so it's more rigourous.\r\n\r\nIt is also the first step for the ownership tokenization. So yes, later, hopefully in 0.15, having the Owner token will mean you can be the control node.\r\nIt's just not that simple because the whole backend works with a community private key right now, so it's not easy changing it to using a user's key instead.",
